Job Description:
We are looking for an experienced Plant General Manager to oversee safety, production, maintenance, and quality assurance at one of our client's largest manufacturing facilities. This role requires leading 800+ employees while ensuring operational excellence, compliance with company objectives, and customer satisfaction. The ideal candidate will be a hands-on operations leader with solid people development skills


Description

* Operational Management: Direct daily production, maintenance, and quality operations while ensuring compliance with company standards and customer requirements
 * Team Leadership: Lead and develop a workforce of 800+ employees, fostering a culture of continuous improvement and operational excellence
 * Budget Management: Control manufacturing costs, maintain operational expenses within budget parameters, and identify cost-reduction opportunities
 * Safety Leadership: Maintain injury-free workplace standards and implement improvements to address safety incidents and near-miss events
 * Performance Optimisation: Utilise lean manufacturing principles and data-driven metrics to identify bottlenecks, reduce costs, and improve overall plant capacity
 * Strategic Planning: Participate in demand planning, production scheduling, and new product launches while collaborating with R&D and product management teams
 * Process Improvement: Implement innovative manufacturing methods and continuous improvement initiatives to achieve error-free production and world-class KPIs


Profile

* Higher degree in Operations Management, Business, Engineering, or related field;
 * 10+ year plant operations or manufacturing engineering experience with proven leadership in medium or large-scale manufacturing environments;
 * Fluency in Vietnamese and English are essential;
 * Current or previous proven experience running sizeable assembly production in Vietnam as Production/Operations Director or Plant GM is a must;
 * Demonstrated ability to develop and lead cross-functional teams as well as to transform organisational performance using lean manufacturing concepts;
 * Proven track record of maintaining safe workplace standards and implementing safety improvement programs
 * Strong analytical and problem-solving abilities with experience in production planning systems and continuous improvement methodologies;
 * Executive presence with ability to communicate complex ideas effectively both verbally and in writing to diverse stakeholders;


Job Offer

Company will provide competitive package and opportunity to develop in global manufacturing network


